# TruffleHog path-exclusion list — Go-regexp patterns, one per line.
#
# IMPORTANT: TruffleHog's --exclude-paths consumes regular expressions
# (not globs). A glob like `dist/**` fails to compile and aborts the
# scan with "could not create exclude rules: can not compile regular
# expression: dist/**". See:
#   https://github.com/trufflesecurity/trufflehog#scanning-options
#
# Each pattern is matched against the file path relative to the repo
# root with Go's regexp/syntax (RE2). Anchor with ^ where helpful.

# Build outputs — anchored so we never match an arbitrary "dist" inside
# a directory name elsewhere in the tree.
^dist/
^packages/spatial-war-room/dist/

# Package lockfiles (integrity SHAs are not rotatable secrets)
^package-lock\.json$
^packages/spatial-war-room/package-lock\.json$

# Installed dependencies
^node_modules/
^packages/[^/]+/node_modules/

# Agent-local scratch / notes (gitignored on purpose, defence-in-depth)
^\.notes/
^\.kovael/
^\.tsupgrader/

# Generated portrait PNGs — binary assets, no source-of-secrets risk.
# Excluded so the binary entropy of color-quantized PNG payload doesn't
# burn CI minutes on every scan; the files themselves are committed.
^packages/spatial-war-room/public/agents/.*\.png$
